latestIgtvVideos.caption:
SLEIGH the holidays with our take on Truffle Blossom Cookies!

Recipe here ⬇️

INGREDIENTS:
1/2 cup white sugar
1/2 cup brown sugar
1/2 cup seed butter or alternative
1 egg
1 1/2 cups flour
3/4 tsp baking soda
1/4 tsp baking powder
1 bag #Thatsit Truffles
1/2 cup extra white sugar

DIRECTIONS:
Preheat oven to 375F. Cream together sugars, butter, seed butter, and egg. Fold in flour, baking soda, and baking powder. Roll cookie dough into balls and dip in white sugar. Place on a baking sheet and bake for 8-10 minutes. Remove cookies from oven and immediately press in chocolate truffle.

Recipe by @emsnutfreeeats

Satisfy your sweet tooth with this Apple Cinnamon Edible Cookie Dough 😋

Recipe here 👇

Ingredients:
1 ½ cups gluten-free flour
½ cup brown sugar
4 tbsp granulated sugar
8 tbsp softened butter
3 tbsp milk
2 tsp vanilla extract
2 tsp cinnamon
½ cup white chocolate chips
3 chopped That’s it. Apple Cinnamon Bars

Directions:
1. Bake flour at 175F on a baking tray for 5 minutes to heat-treat.
2. Cream together butter, granulated & brown sugar, vanilla extract and milk. 
3. Fold in cinnamon and heat-treated flour, then mix in chopped #Thatsit bars and white chocolate chips!
